      "rationale": "Commercial FEA solver (Ansys Mechanical) used by all three modelling teams is covered by vendor-supplied V&V documentation and ISO 9001 quality management. Internal SQA procedures documented for FDA and DePuy Synthes teams. Required Gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems from the Ansys Verification Manual and NAFEMS benchmarks were executed and results compared to analytical solutions. Residual norms confirmed below solver tolerance. Required Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study conducted across three element sizes (coarse, medium, fine) for each team's model. Richardson extrapolation applied; discretization error in peak von Mises stress estimated below 3%. Required Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver convergence criteria set to 1e-6 relative residual. Contact penetration tolerance verified. No divergence or hourglassing observed across all simulation runs. Required Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Modelling protocols reviewed by an independent analyst at each participating organisation. Boundary condition application and material assignment verified against written simulation plan prior to execution. Required Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic constitutive model with frictional contact at screw-rod interface adopted by all teams. Justification for linearity supported by load-displacement linearity observed experimentally up to 60% of failure load. Required Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (Ti-6Al-4V: E=114 GPa, ν=0.34) sourced from ASTM F136 coupon testing. Geometric dimensions measured from coordinate measuring machine data on representative hardware. Torque preload on set screws measured and incorporated. Required Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. Lot traceability documented; dimensional inspection confirmed conformance to design nominal. Sample size adequate for comparison at Gradation 3. Required level satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single load level (compression-bending at 10 Nm) per ASTM F1717. Only one test condition was evaluated, precluding Gradation 3 multi-condition coverage. This factor falls below the required level and is flagged as a credibility gap. Required Gradation 3 NOT satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Simulation inputs mapped one-to-one to experimental test configuration: fixture geometry, offset distance, applied displacement rate, and torque preload all replicated in the FEA boundary conditions. Equivalency confirmed by cross-team review. Required Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Predicted construct stiffness and peak load at 2% offset compared against experimental mean ± SD. All three FEA teams within 10% of experimental mean; no outliers. Quantitative comparison metric (normalised error) computed and reported. Required Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Quantities of interest (construct stiffness, peak bending load) are directly specified in ASTM F1717 and are the quantities used in pre-market regulatory submissions. Clinical relevance to fatigue life prediction justified by linear-elastic stress as input to Goodman diagram analysis. Required Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities replicate the exact ASTM F1717 test configuration used in device submissions. Hardware, fixturing, and loading protocol identical to intended regulatory use. Validation domain overlap with intended use assessed as high. Required Gradation 3 satisfied."
    }
